We can also calculate directly the detectivity (D*) of our photodetectors as shown in Fig. 8(b). The detectivity (D*) characterizes the capability of a photodetector to detect the weakest light signal34. In general, the detectivity can be calculated from the relation31,33:1D⁎=AR2qId\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
